 The special task force maintaining peace in Plateau and some parts of Bauchi and Kaduna states, Operation Safe Haven (OPSH), has trained 122 youth to assist the security agencies to ensure security in the communities of Sanga LGA of Kaduna State. Sanga is among the LGAs in Southern Kaduna that has been suffering attacks by gunmen in recent times. Delivering his remarks on Saturday at their passing out, the special guest of honour, Major General Ibrahim Ali, who is the commander of the operation, charged the youths to take the lead in ensuring timely security information got to the security agencies for prompt action.